original: Bluegills can grow up to 12 inches (30 cm) long and about 4+1?2 pounds (2.0 kg). While their color can vary from population to population, they typically have a very distinctive coloring, with deep blue and purple on the face and gill cover, dark olive-colored bands down the side, and a fiery orange to yellow belly. The fish are omnivores and will eat anything they can fit in their mouth. They mostly feed on small aquatic insects and fish. The fish play a key role in the food chain, and are prey for bass, other sunfish, northern pike, walleye, muskies, trout, and snapping turtles

original: The White Bass is a freshwater fish of the temperate bass family Moronidae. The species' main color is silver-white to pale green. Its back is dark, with white sides and belly, and with narrow dark stripes running lengthwise on its sides. It has large, rough scales and two dorsal fins. The more anterior dorsal fin is much harder and appears to have spines on them. Although these are not true spines, this type of fin is called a spinous ray. The more posterior of the two dorsal fins is much softer, and is thus called a soft-ray.

Спина у него темная, с белыми боками и брюхом и с узкими темными полосами, идущими вдоль по бокам. У него крупная грубая чешуя и два спинных плавника. La più posteriore delle due pinne dorsali è molto più morbida ed è quindi chiamata raggio molle.

original: The brook trout (Salvelinus fontinalis) is a species of freshwater fish in the char genus Salvelinus of the salmon family Salmonidae. It is native to Eastern North America in the United States and Canada, but has been introduced elsewhere in North America, as well as to Iceland, Europe, and Asia. In parts of its range, it is also known as the eastern brook trout, speckled trout, brook charr, squaretail, brookie or mud trout, among others. A potamodromous population in Lake Superior, as well as an anadromous population in Maine, is known as coaster trout or, simply, as coasters. The brook trout is the state fish of nine U.S. states: Michigan, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, North Carolina, Pennsylvania, Vermont, Virginia, and West Virginia, and the Provincial Fish of Nova Scotia in Canada.

chinesesimp: 美洲红点鲑是鲑科鲑属中的一种淡水鱼。它原产于美国和加拿大的北美东部，但已被引入北美其他地方，以及冰岛、欧洲和亚洲。在其范围的一部分，它也被称为东方溪鳟，斑点鳟，溪charr，方尾，brookie或泥鳟，等等。苏必利尔湖的一个溯河种群，以及缅因州的一个溯河种群，被称为海岸鳟，或者简称为海岸鳟。溪鳟是美国九个州的州鱼:密歇根、新罕布什尔、新泽西、纽约、北卡罗来纳、宾夕法尼亚、佛蒙特、弗吉尼亚和西弗吉尼亚，以及加拿大新斯科舍的省鱼。

original: The cutthroat trout (Oncorhynchus clarkii) is a fish species of the family Salmonidae native to cold-water tributaries of the Pacific Ocean, Rocky Mountains, and Great Basin in North America. As a member of the genus Oncorhynchus, it is one of the Pacific trout, a group that includes the widely distributed rainbow trout. Cutthroat trout are popular gamefish, especially among anglers who enjoy fly fishing. The common name "cutthroat" refers to the distinctive red coloration on the underside of the lower jaw. The specific name clarkii was given to honor explorer William Clark, coleader of the Lewis and Clark Expedition.

french: La truite fardée (Oncorhynchus clarkii) est une espèce de poisson de la famille des Salmonidae originaires de affluents d'eau froide de l'océan Pacifique, des montagnes rocheuses et du grand bassin en Amérique du Nord. En tant que membre du genre Oncorhynchus, c'est l'une des truites du Pacifique, un groupe qui comprend la truite arc-en-ciel largement distribuée. La truite fardée est un poisson de jeu populaire, en particulier parmi les pêcheurs qui aiment la pêche à la mouche.

chinesesimp: 美洲鲑(克氏虹鳟)是鲑科的一种鱼类，原产于太平洋、落基山脉和北美大盆地的冷水支流。作为Oncorhynchus属的一员，它是太平洋鳟鱼的一种，包括广泛分布的虹鳟鱼。割喉鳟鱼是受欢迎的游戏鱼，尤其是喜欢飞钓的垂钓者。俗称“割喉”是指下颌下侧与众不同的红色。克拉克ii这个特别的名字是为了纪念探险家威廉・克拉克，他是路易斯和克拉克探险队的队长。

original: The lake trout (Salvelinus namaycush) is a freshwater char living mainly in lakes in northern North America. Other names for it include mackinaw, namaycush, lake char (or charr), touladi, togue, and grey trout. In Lake Superior, it can also be variously known as siscowet, paperbelly and lean. The lake trout is prized both as a game fish and as a food fish. Those caught with dark coloration may be called mud hens.

french: Le lac Trout (Salvelinus Namaycush) est un charbon douce vivant principalement dans les lacs du nord de l'Amérique du Nord. Les autres noms comprennent Mackinaw, Namaycush, le lac Char (ou Charr), Touladi, Togue et la truite grise. Dans le lac Supérieur, il peut également être connu sous le nom de siscowet, de papier et de maigre. Le truite du lac est prisé à la fois comme un poisson de gibier et comme un poisson alimentaire. Ceux pris avec une coloration foncée peuvent être appelés poules de boue.

chinesesimp: 湖鳟是一种主要生活在北美洲北部湖泊中的淡水鱼。其他名称包括灰鳟。在苏必利尔湖，它也可以被称为剑麻、纸腹和瘦。湖鳟鱼既被视为猎物，也被视为食用鱼。那些颜色较深的可能被称为泥鸡。

portuguese: The sockeye salmon (Oncorhynchus nerka), also called red salmon, kokanee salmon, blueback salmon, or simply sockeye, is an anadromous species of salmon found in the Northern Pacific Ocean and rivers discharging into it. This species is a Pacific salmon that is primarily red in hue during spawning. They can grow up to 84 cm (2 ft 9 in) in length and weigh 2.3 to 7 kg (5C15 lb). Juveniles remain in freshwater until they are ready to migrate to the ocean, over distances of up to 1,600 km (1,000 mi). Their diet consists primarily of zooplankton. Sockeye salmon are semelparous, dying after they spawn. Some populations, referred to as kokanee, do not migrate to the ocean and live their entire lives in fresh water.
chinesesimp: 金鳟也称为红鲑鱼、肯氏红大马哈鱼、蓝背鲑鱼或简称为红鲑，是北太平洋和流入太平洋的河流中发现的溯河产卵的鲑鱼品种。这是一种太平洋鲑鱼，产卵时主要呈红色。它们可以长到84厘米（2英尺9英寸）长，重2.3至7公斤（5-15磅）。幼鱼会一直呆在淡水中，直到它们准备好迁徙到1600公里（1000英里）以外的海洋。它们的食物主要是浮游动物。红鲑是假尾鲑，产卵后死亡。一些被称为kokanee的种群不会迁徙到海洋，它们一生都生活在淡水中。

Juveniles remain in freshwater until they are ready to migrate to the ocean, over distances of up to 1,600 km (1,000 mi). Their diet consists primarily of zooplankton. Sockeye salmon are semelparous, dying after they spawn. Some populations, referred to as kokanee, do not migrate to the ocean and live their entire lives in fresh water.

french: Le saumon rouges (Oncorhynchus nerka), également appelé saumon rouge, saumon kokanee, saumon à dos bleu ou simplement saumon, est une espèce anadrome de saumon trouvée dans l'océan Pacifique du Nord et les rivières qui y déchargement. Cette espèce est un saumon du Pacifique qui est principalement rouge dans la teinte pendant le frai. Ils peuvent atteindre 84 cm de long et peser 2,3 à 7 kg. Les juvéniles restent dans l'eau douce jusqu'à ce qu'ils soient prêts à migrer vers l'océan, sur des distances allant jusqu'à 1 600 km. Leur régime se compose principalement de zooplancton. Le saumon rouges est sèche, mourant après avoir frayé. Certaines populations, appelées Kokanee, ne migrent pas vers l'océan et vivent toute leur vie dans l'eau douce.

portuguese: The Chinook salmon Oncorhynchus tshawytscha) is the largest and most valuable species of Pacific salmon in North America, as well as the largest in the genus Oncorhynchus. Its common name is derived from the Chinookan peoples. Other vernacular names for the species include king salmon, Quinnat salmon, Tsumen, spring salmon, chrome hog, Blackmouth, and Tyee salmon. The scientific species name is based on the Russian common name chavycha.

original: Lobsters are a family of large marine crustaceans. Lobsters have long bodies with muscular tails, and live in crevices or burrows on the sea floor. Three of their five pairs of legs have claws, including the first pair, which are usually much larger than the others.

french: Le bar à petite bouche (Micropterus Dolomieu) est une espèce de poisson d'eau douce dans la famille des poissons-sols (Centrarchidae) de l'Ordre Perciformes. Il s'agit de l'espèce type de son genre Micropterus (basses noires), et est un poisson de jeu populaire recherché par les pêcheurs dans les zones tempérées de l'Amérique du Nord, et s'est propagée par le stockage - ainsi que des introductions illégales - à de nombreux affluents d'eau cool-eau et les lacs au Canada et plus encore introduits aux états-Unis.

original: The smallmouth bass (Micropterus dolomieu) is a species of freshwater fish in the sunfish family (Centrarchidae) of the order Perciformes. It is the type species of its genus Micropterus (black basses), and is a popular game fish sought by anglers throughout the temperate zones of North America, and has been spread by stocking―as well as illegal introductions―to many cool-water tributaries and lakes in Canada and more so introduced in the United States.

original: Centrarchidae, better known as sunfishes, is a family of freshwater ray-finned fish belonging to the order Perciformes (formerly belonging to the deprecated order Centrarchiformes), native only to North America. There are eight universally included genera within the centrarchid family: Lepomis (true sunfishes), Micropterus (black basses), Pomoxis (crappies), Enneacanthus (banded sunfishes), Centrarchus (type genus, consisting solely of the flier C. macropterus), Archoplites (Sacramento perch), Ambloplites (rock basses), and Acantharchus (mud sunfish).

french: La m?le ou poisson-lune (Mola mola) est une espèce de poissons de la famille des Molidae. Sa masse dépasse communément la tonne et peut atteindre 2 744 kilogrammes, ce qui en fait le plus lourd de tous les poissons osseux. On la trouve dans les eaux tropicales et tempérées tout autour du monde. C'est un animal à la tête proéminente, sans queue et latéralement aplati. Nageoires dorsale et anale comprises, une m?le peut être aussi haute que longue.

chinesesimp: 中央鱼科，更为人所知的是太阳鱼，是一科淡水射线鳍鱼，属于鲈形目以前属于已弃用的中央鱼目，原产于北美洲。中鳍鱼科有八个普遍包括的属：真太阳鱼、黑鲈鱼、克拉皮鱼、带状太阳鱼，模式属，仅由大鳍飞鱼组成、萨克拉门托鲈鱼、岩鲈鱼和泥太阳鱼。

original: The walleye (Sander vitreus, synonym Stizostedion vitreum), also called the yellow pike or yellow pickerel, is a freshwater perciform fish native to most of Canada and to the Northern United States. It is a North American close relative of the European zander, also known as the pikeperch. The walleye is sometimes called the yellow walleye to distinguish it from the blue walleye, which is a color morph that was once found in the southern Ontario and Quebec regions, but is now presumed extinct.
